NSO_A2 Ansible Deployment
=========================

This repository contains:
- `hosts` inventory required by the assignment
- `site.yaml` playbook to deploy Flask app + HAProxy and run a basic test

How it works
------------
1. Clones/updates `https://github.com/patrikarlos/NSO_A2.git` on `devA`, `devB`, `devC`.
2. Runs `/opt/NSO_A2/application2.py` (from that repo) as the Flask service.
3. Configures HAProxy on host `HAproxy` to load-balance across all three backends.
4. Sends 3 HTTP requests to HAProxy endpoint and verifies all backend hosts answered.

SSH jump host configuration
---------------------------
runs with:

`ansible-playbook --ssh-common-args "-F /home/joedoe/.ssh/include/NSO_$tag" -i hosts site.yaml`

The SSH config include file must define jump behavior. Example:

```sshconfig
Host bastionNSO
    HostName <BASTION_PUBLIC_IP>
    User ubuntu
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/<your_private_key>

Host HAproxy devA devB devC
    User ubuntu
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/<your_private_key>
    ProxyJump bastionNSO
```

Run
---

```bash
ansible-playbook --ssh-common-args "-F /home/joedoe/.ssh/include/NSO_$tag" -i hosts site.yaml
```

Notes
-----
- Ubuntu 20.04 compatible.(OPTIMIZED ESPECIALLY!)
